<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 23 at 4:30AM EST  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...PATCHY BLACK ICE THIS MORNING ACROSS PARTS OF THE WESTERN
PIEDMONT OF NORTH CAROLINA...
Any runoff from snow melt yesterday will refreeze on untreated
road surfaces this morning as the temperature remains below
freezing. As a result, patchy black ice may be encountered on some
area roadways through mid-morning. Watch out for slippery spots
on roads. Temperatures should warm back above freezing around 10
AM.</description>
